## Security Architecture

### SSL/TLS Encryption

**Certificate Authority:**
- FreeIPA configured as internal Certificate Authority
- Issues X.509 certificates for all services
- Centralized trust chain management
- 2-year certificate validity

**SSL Implementation:**
- Nginx handles SSL/TLS termination
- TLS 1.2 and TLS 1.3 enabled
- Strong cipher suites only (ECDHE, AES-GCM)
- Perfect Forward Secrecy enabled
- HTTP automatically redirects to HTTPS

**Certificate Structure:**
- apps.lab.local certificate with Subject Alternative Names (SANs)
  - Covers 6 services on application VM
- mntr.lab.local certificate with SANs
  - Covers 2 services on monitoring VM
- Certificates stored at `/etc/nginx/ssl/` on respective hosts

### Secrets Management

**Two-Tier Architecture:**

**Tier 1: Vaultwarden (Human Access)**
- Self-hosted password manager
- End-to-end encryption
- Master password protected
- Folder-organized credentials
- Browser extension support
- Mobile app compatibility

**Tier 2: Ansible Vault (Automation)**
- AES256 encrypted secrets file
- Infrastructure credentials stored as variables
- Vault password stored in Vaultwarden
- Automated decryption via password file
- Version-controlled (encrypted state)

**Environment Variable Flow:**
Ansible Vault (encrypted)
↓
Generate .env files (plaintext, 0600 perms)
↓
Docker Compose reads environment variables
↓
Containers receive credentials at runtime
**Security Controls:**
- No hardcoded passwords in code
- Secrets encrypted at rest
- Strict file permissions (0600)
- .gitignore protection
- Regular password rotation (90-180 days)

### Authentication & Authorization

**Centralized Authentication:**
- FreeIPA provides single sign-on (SSO)
- LDAP backend for user directory
- Kerberos for authentication
- Automated password policies
- Account lockout protection

**Role-Based Access Control:**
- User groups for permission management
- Sudo rules enforced centrally
- Host-based access control
- Service account separation

